dcterms:description: The MIT-BIH Arrhythmia Database contains sections of ambulatory ECG recordings from 47 subjects, digitized at 360 samples per second per channel with 11-bit resolution at 10-mV range on two channels. It is frequently used for time-series classification research and has been pre-annotated and labelled by cardiologists.
dcterms:title: MIT-BIH Arrhythmia Database
